---
// Three ILLUSTRATIVE snapshots of what the running summary might say across a
// "log in" session — turn 1 / ~8 / ~20. Not captured output; hand-written to
// show the arc: thin → working theory → records a dead end → narrows → near done.
const snapshots = [
  {
    label: 'Turn 1',
    body: 'Just started. Goal: log in. Landed on what looks like a home screen — there’s a Sign in affordance top-right (node #41). No form visible yet. Plan: tap it.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Turn ~8',
    body: 'On the login form (route /auth). Email field is node #112, password #118, submit #124. A first submit with a clearly-bogus email was rejected inline (“enter a valid email”) — the field validates on submit, not on blur. Retrying with a well-formed address.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Turn ~20',
    body: 'Logged in — landed on /home with a populated feed (8 list items) and an avatar in the app bar that wasn’t there before. The email-format rejection was the only snag. Goal looks met; one more turn to confirm the session survives a route change, then done.',
  },
];
---
<div class="snapshots">
  {snapshots.map((s) => (
    <figure class="note">
      <figcaption class="note-head">
        <span class="turn mono">{s.label}</span>
        <span class="badge">Illustrative</span>
      </figcaption>
      <blockquote class="note-body">{s.body}</blockquote>
    </figure>
  ))}
</div>
<p class="caption">
  The harness never writes this. The model does — once per turn, in its own
  words. It’s the closest thing the agent has to a memory that isn’t just “the
  last few things I did” or “what I’m looking at right now.” (Text above is
  illustrative, not captured output.)
</p>

<style>
  .snapshots {
    margin: 24px 0 12px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .note {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--tier-amber);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    background: rgba(247, 200, 115, 0.05);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .note-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .turn { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--tier-amber); font-weight: 600; }
  .badge {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 1px 8px;
  }
  .note-body {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .caption { margin: 14px 0 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.55; }
</style>
